HEADWORD: Cognizor
<hw>Cog`ni*zor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Cognizance</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>One who acknowledged
the right of the plaintiff or cognizee in a fine; the defendant.</def>
<rj><au>Blackstone.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
